div2.p:
This coin belongs to Hill's Fourth Series, which he dates from the 1st century after Christ to about 224 A.D.;
                  Oxathres is assigned by him to the 1st c. B.C. De Morgan (Manuel, p. 271) places Piruz I (=
                  Pakur?) immediately after Oxathres (perhaps Gocithres of Isidore of Charax), and he dates the latter ca. 57–38 B.C.

